                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol of Hackney. On the 8th of August, at four o'clock in the morning, I was in Hackney Marsh; I saw the prisoner walking backward and forward by the river, with something on his back - I went to him and asked what it was - he said his own tools - that he came from High Wycombe, and would answer no more questions. I found a basket on his back containing these tools.</p>
               <p>
            
